The paper focuses on building a knowledge graph for program code, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of generic code analysis techniques and documentation from StackOverflow suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The application of the knowledge graph to diverse tasks such as code understanding and automation suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
